data_violence_region <- data |>
  group_by(Year,area) |>
  summarize(gpi=weighted.mean(x=gpi,w=pop,na.rm = FALSE)) 
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'Year'. You can override using the
## `.groups` argument.

Step 1:
data widepivot_longer() long
sex life_exp 

data_life_exp_region <- data |>
  pivot_longer(
    !c('Year','iso3','pop','area','gpi','country'),  # 
    names_to = 'sex',       #  'sex' 
    values_to = 'life_exp'  #  'life_exp' 
  ) |>
  
  #  Step 2: 
  # "life_exp_male", "life_exp_female"10
  # "male"  "female" 
  mutate(sex = substr(sex, 10, length(sex))) |>
  
  #  Step 3: 
  group_by(Year, area, sex) |>
  summarize(
    life_exp = weighted.mean(x = life_exp, w = pop, na.rm = FALSE)  # , na.rm = NATRUE
  )
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'Year', 'area'. You can override using the
## `.groups` argument.

:

Step 4:

8 Question 7

20082023

Step 1: 

data_high <- data |>
  filter(Year %in% c(2008, 2023)) |>          # 20082023
  select(Year, country, area, gpi) |>         # 
  pivot_wider(
    names_from = 'Year',                      # Year 
    values_from = 'gpi'                       #  GPI
  ) |>
  mutate(
    var = (`2023` - `2008`) / `2008`          # 
  ) |>
  group_by(area) |>                           # 
  slice_max(var, n = 5) |>                    # 5
  mutate(label = 'Highest Violence Increase') #

Step 2: 

data_low <- data |>
  filter(Year %in% c(2008, 2023)) |>          # 
  select(Year, country, area, gpi) |>
  pivot_wider(names_from = 'Year', values_from = 'gpi') |>
  mutate(
    var = (`2023` - `2008`) / `2008`
  ) |>
  group_by(area) |>
  slice_min(var, n = 5) |>                    # 5
  mutate(label = 'Highest Violence Decrease')

Step 3: 2

plot_data <- rbind(data_high, data_low)
# rbind() =

Step 4: 

plot7 <- plot_data |>
  filter(area == 'Northern Africa and Western Asia') |>  # 
  ggplot(
    aes(
      x = reorder(country, var),   # 
      y = var,                     # Y = 
      fill = label                 #  or 
    )
  ) +
  
  geom_bar(stat = 'identity') +               # 
  theme_clean() +                             # 
  xlab('Country') +                           # X
  ylab('Variation in Violence') +             # Y
  scale_fill_brewer(name = '', palette = 'Set2') +  # 
  scale_y_continuous(labels = scales::percent) +    # 
  
  #  Step 5: 
  theme(
    axis.text.x = element_text(
      angle = 45, vjust = 1, hjust = 1,
      size = 12, face = "bold"
    ),
    legend.position = 'bottom',
    axis.text.y = element_text(size = 12, face = "bold"),
    axis.title.x = element_text(size = 15, face = "bold"),
    axis.title.y = element_text(size = 15, face = "bold"),
    legend.text = element_text(size = 15, face = "bold")
  )

model <- lm(
  life_exp ~ gpi + sex + area,
  data    = data_scatter,
  weights = pop
)
